# Frontend Rules — BundleIQ (HTMX + Tailwind)

## Zero Build Step Philosophy
No npm. No webpack. No node_modules. No TypeScript compilation.
Everything via CDN tags in `layout.html`. If you need a JS library, it must be available on unpkg.com or cdnjs.

## Required CDN Tags (in layout.html <head>)
```html
<script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
<script src="https://unpkg.com/htmx.org@2.0.0" integrity="sha384-..." crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
<script src="https://unpkg.com/htmx-ext-sse@2.2.1/sse.js"></script>
```

## HTMX SSE Pattern (copy exactly for each streaming panel)
```html
<!-- Each panel connects to its own SSE endpoint -->
<!-- The hx-ext="sse" must be on a PARENT of the sse-swap target -->
<div hx-ext="sse" sse-connect="/stream/{{.SessionID}}/triage">
    <div id="triage-content" 
         sse-swap="triage-update"
         hx-swap="innerHTML">
        <!-- Loading skeleton shown until first event -->
        <div class="animate-pulse space-y-3">
            <div class="h-4 bg-gray-200 rounded w-3/4"></div>
            <div class="h-4 bg-gray-200 rounded w-1/2"></div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- RCA panel: streaming text that appends -->
<div hx-ext="sse" sse-connect="/stream/{{.SessionID}}/rca">
    <div id="rca-content"
         sse-swap="rca-chunk"
         hx-swap="beforeend">
        <!-- New chunks append here -->
    </div>
</div>
```

## HTMX Forms and Actions
```html
<!-- Upload form -->
<form hx-post="/upload"
      hx-encoding="multipart/form-data"
      hx-target="#upload-result"
      hx-swap="innerHTML"
      hx-indicator="#upload-spinner">
    
    <input type="file" name="bundle" accept=".tar.gz,.tgz" class="hidden" id="file-input">
    
    <!-- Custom drop zone (clicks the hidden input) -->
    <div id="drop-zone"
         class="border-2 border-dashed border-gray-300 rounded-xl p-16 text-center cursor-pointer
                hover:border-blue-400 hover:bg-blue-50 transition-colors"
         onclick="document.getElementById('file-input').click()">
        <p class="text-gray-500">Drop your support bundle here</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">.tar.gz up to 250MB</p>
    </div>
    
    <!-- Spinner (hidden by default, shown via htmx-request class) -->
    <div id="upload-spinner" class="htmx-indicator flex items-center gap-2">
        <div class="animate-spin h-5 w-5 border-2 border-blue-500 border-t-transparent rounded-full"></div>
        <span>Uploading...</span>
    </div>
</form>
```

## Tailwind Color System for BundleIQ
Use these semantic color conventions consistently:

```
Critical/Error:  bg-red-50, text-red-700, border-red-200
Warning/High:    bg-amber-50, text-amber-700, border-amber-200  
Info/Medium:     bg-blue-50, text-blue-700, border-blue-200
Success/Low:     bg-green-50, text-green-700, border-green-200
Neutral:         bg-gray-50, text-gray-700, border-gray-200
```

Severity score colors:
```
Score 70-100 (Critical):  text-red-600 bg-red-50
Score 40-69  (Warning):   text-amber-600 bg-amber-50
Score 0-39   (Healthy):   text-green-600 bg-green-50
```

