## JavaScript Rules
- Minimal JavaScript — prefer HTMX attributes for everything
- Small `<script>` blocks are OK for: copy-to-clipboard, drag-drop events, auto-scroll
- No external JS libraries except what's already in CDN tags
- No `fetch()` API calls — use HTMX `hx-post`, `hx-get` etc.

### Copy to Clipboard (the only allowed custom JS pattern)
```html
<button onclick="navigator.clipboard.writeText(this.dataset.text)" 
        data-text="kubectl get pods -n default"
        class="text-xs text-gray-400 hover:text-gray-600">
    Copy
</button>
```

### Auto-scroll chat to bottom
```html
<script>
// Called after each new chat message is inserted
function scrollChatToBottom() {
    const chat = document.getElementById('chat-messages');
    if (chat) chat.scrollTop = chat.scrollHeight;
}
// HTMX after-swap hook
document.body.addEventListener('htmx:afterSwap', function(e) {
    if (e.detail.target.id === 'chat-messages') scrollChatToBottom();
});
</script>
```

## Go Template Patterns
```html
<!-- Always escape user data -->
{{html .UserProvidedContent}}

<!-- Conditional classes -->
<div class="{{if .IsError}}text-red-600{{else}}text-gray-600{{end}}">

<!-- Range with index -->
{{range $i, $event := .Events}}
    {{if $i}}<div class="border-t border-gray-100"></div>{{end}}
    <!-- event content -->
{{end}}

<!-- Template blocks for layout -->
{{block "content" .}}{{end}}

<!-- Call sub-templates with dot -->
{{template "severity-badge" .Severity}}
```

## Layout Structure
```
layout.html
├── <html lang="en">
│   ├── <head> with all CDN tags, meta, title
│   └── <body class="bg-gray-50 min-h-screen">
│       ├── Stub mode banner (conditional)
│       ├── <nav> with logo + nav links
│       ├── <main> — {{block "content" .}}{{end}}
│       └── small <script> block for global JS
```

## Accessibility
- All icons need aria-label or are aria-hidden="true" with adjacent text
- Form inputs need associated `<label>` elements
- Color is never the ONLY indicator of meaning (add text or icon too)
- Focus states must be visible (use `focus:ring-2` Tailwind classes)
